    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-11-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-11-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="1156"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1156">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/38.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1462.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-11-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 10, 1913.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your No. 2099, of
                    October 20, transmitting two notes from your Spanish colleague in regard to the
                    recent outrages against Spaniards in northern Mexico.</p>
                <p>In reply you are instructed to say to the Spanish Minister that the Department
                    has made representations which it is hoped will result in the protection of
                    Spanish subjects in Mexico and in the punishment of those persons who have
                    committed the outrages referred to.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. B. Moore</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
